alwaysApply: true
---

- Follow the official Kotlin style guide strictly: https://developer.android.com/kotlin/style-guide
- Use camelCase for variables and functions.
- Use PascalCase for classes and objects.
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants.
- Prefer val over var when possible.
- Use meaningful, self-documenting names.
- Keep functions small and focused; use expression bodies for simple functions.
- Prefer data classes for data containers.
- Use extension functions appropriately.
- Adhere to Kotlin idioms and conventions for readability, consistency, and maintainability.
